    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 129.</p><p>Patron’s Blast</p><p>10th-level evocation</p><p>Classes: Warlock Casting Time: 1 action Range: Self (240-foot line) Components: V Duration: Instantaneous</p><p>You speak a word of power and release the full, unrestrained might of your patron in a catastrophic burst of disintegrating energy. A 240-foot long, 10-foot wide line of raw magical force erupts from you, its color and shape a reflection of your patron’s nature–a wall of hellfire, a celestial streak of silver light, an eldritch tide of writhing darkness.</p><p>Each creature in the line must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 8d10 x 10 force damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one. A creature that fails this saving throw by 5 or more is also incapacitated until the end of its next turn, as the blast tears through it. If this damage reduces a creature to 0 hit points, it is disintegrated. A disintegrated creature, along with everything it wears and carries except magic items, is reduced to a pile of fine gray dust. A disintegrated creature can only be restored to life by a True Resurrection or Wish spell.</p><p>This spell automatically destroys Large or smaller nonmagical objects and creations of magical force. If the target is a Huge or larger object or a creation of force, the spell destroys a 10-foot-cube portion of it. Rare or rarer magic items are not destroyed.</p></div>",
